00:11:52.760 --> 00:11:56.570
It is the instrumentality
of a death.

00:11:56.570 --> 00:12:01.300
So if a tree branch falls off you
-- falls off a tree and hits you,

00:12:01.300 --> 00:12:03.050
then the tree branch is a dayadand.

00:12:03.050 --> 00:12:07.190
If a wagon kills you, then
the wagon is the dayadand.

00:12:07.190 --> 00:12:09.490
You know, if a donkey
kills you, then you know,

00:12:09.490 --> 00:12:10.790
the donkey is the dayadand.

00:12:10.790 --> 00:12:14.200
And under the law of dayadands
-- there was a law for this --

00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:19.400
all dayadands were forfeit to the
crown and were usually destroyed.

00:12:19.400 --> 00:12:24.060
In this odd, sort of
-- you know, end.

00:12:24.060 --> 00:12:26.940
So this is a landscape
with dayadand.

00:12:26.940 --> 00:12:32.110
"A road in the trees
from the sound of it.

00:12:32.110 --> 00:12:36.940
A milky shift in the water
where the silt shelves down.

00:12:36.940 --> 00:12:40.010
And the wet branch,
beating for its life

00:12:40.010 --> 00:12:42.600
against the pages of that book."

00:12:42.600 --> 00:12:47.080 position:56%
