00:13:02.570 --> 00:13:05.350
and those -- for those of you
non-lawyers in the room --

00:13:05.350 --> 00:13:09.050
Black Acre is a legal placeholder
term for a piece of property

00:13:09.050 --> 00:13:13.840 position:56%
or an estate, the way John Doe is a
legal placeholder term for a person.

00:13:13.840 --> 00:13:17.060
So often times in your
property law class, and trust

00:13:17.060 --> 00:13:21.390
and estates you'll get, you know,
John Doe transfers his property,

00:13:21.390 --> 00:13:24.970
Black Acre to Jane
Roe in consideration

00:13:24.970 --> 00:13:27.280
for her property, White Acre.

00:13:27.280 --> 00:13:29.850
And there's a kind of
sequence to the hypothetical.

00:13:29.850 --> 00:13:33.650
So it'll just spin out as, Black
Acre, White Acre, Blue Acre,

00:13:33.650 --> 00:13:38.370
Green Acre, Brown Acre -- I
added Red Acre and Gold Acre just

00:13:38.370 --> 00:13:40.190
because I could [laughs].

00:13:40.190 --> 00:13:42.630
Poetic license, you know?

00:13:42.630 --> 00:13:45.360
And so I thought -- and
I was thinking about --

00:13:45.360 --> 00:13:49.700
I used the thought of the acre
to think about what is given

00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:51.200
and what is transformable.

00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:53.240
A piece of land is an
interesting metaphor.

00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:54.730
Because you have a
certain pied of land

00:13:54.730 --> 00:13:56.350
and there are things
you can do with it.

00:13:56.350 --> 00:13:58.930
You could sell it to a
shopping mall developer.

00:13:58.930 --> 00:14:00.230
You could build a house.

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:01.590
You can plant a garden.

00:14:01.590 --> 00:14:03.090
You can make a home.

00:14:03.090 --> 00:14:05.200
You could dig a grave.

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:07.080
You could make it into your legacy.

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:09.230
But there are certain things
you can transform about it;

00:14:09.230 --> 00:14:11.710
there are certain things you
cannot transform about it.

00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:15.230
At some point in dealing with
a piece of land, you know,

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:19.420
what we are allotted, we come up
against the concept of the given.

00:14:19.420 --> 00:14:21.800
You know, what cannot
be transformed.

00:14:21.800 --> 00:14:27.280
And what we pass on to
those who come after us.

00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:30.660
And so I was -- you know, a
lot of these acre poems ended

00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:35.570
