oh God, I'm going to have
to look up the translation.

00:15:07.280 --> 00:15:11.920
I got very little -- yes, it's
"He favors our undertaking".

00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:16.600
So -- and it references
the myth of cadmos.

00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:19.540
A cadmos, for those of you
who are mythology buffs,

00:15:19.540 --> 00:15:21.910 position:56%
is the legendary founder of thieves.

00:15:21.910 --> 00:15:27.760
So his sister, Europa, is
kidnapped by Zeus, the white bull.

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:30.020
And so he goes off looking
for her, and he completely --

00:15:30.020 --> 00:15:35.070
and he fails to find her, but
instead he decides to found a city.

00:15:35.070 --> 00:15:36.660
He's told by an oracle to do this.

00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:40.290
And so he kills a dragon, and
he sews the dragon's teeth

00:15:40.290 --> 00:15:43.280 position:56%
in the ground -- this might be
starting to sound a little familiar.

00:15:43.280 --> 00:15:45.370
And these armed men spring up.

00:15:45.370 --> 00:15:48.070
And the -- and he doesn't --
he's afraid of the armed men,

00:15:48.070 --> 00:15:50.170
so he throws a rock
into their midst.

00:15:50.170 --> 00:15:53.740
And I'm kind of using this to
think about the way in which --

00:15:53.740 --> 00:16:00.140
the unthinking way in which we want
money to be fruitful; to multiply.

00:16:00.140 --> 00:16:03.420
The judge I clerked for was
obsessed with the notion of usury.

00:16:03.420 --> 00:16:06.920
An sort of, so am I.

00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:09.240
Green acre.

00:16:09.240 --> 00:16:14.830 position:56%
But what if a given surface is
coaxed into fruitfulness wrongfully?

00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:17.760
For instance, this
lushly verdant plane.

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:20.680
Imagine it dialed back
to featurelessness.

00:16:20.680 --> 00:16:23.360
Each spiraling stock retracted.

00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:26.690
Each filigree rosette
slow-blinking shut.

00:16:26.690 --> 00:16:30.990
Dialed back to bare promise;
to smooth napped expanse.

00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:35.240
The forehead of an alien princess
might convey such tranquility.

00:16:35.240 --> 00:16:37.540
She surveys her ranks of suitors.

00:16:37.540 --> 00:16:42.320
Shakes her exquisite green head
in scarcely feigned regret.

00:16:42.320 --> 00:16:45.920
So thinks Cadmos, hands
still outstretched

00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:48.190
in a nation-building gesture.

00:16:48.190 --> 00:16:50.760
As if to freeze in
time this instant.

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:53.120
Scatter of seeds still aloft.

00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:56.220
Arrayed like little dive
bombers information.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:58.710
Not yet puncturing the land.

00:16:58.710 --> 00:17:00.040
Not yet rooting.

00:17:00.040 --> 00:17:04.900 position:56%
Not yet sending up terribly thin,
ambitious tendrils toward the light.

00:17:04.900 --> 00:17:07.770
Not yet trained onto
wire frame espaliers.

00:17:07.770 --> 00:17:11.000
Not combed into bombastic
pompadours.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:14.810
Not yet extruding seed pods
resembling pale grapes;

00:17:14.810 --> 00:17:16.600
resembling pearls.

00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:23.080
The root of remorse isn't tooth,
he recalls abruptly, but to bite

00:17:23.080 --> 00:17:29.800
and then stoops, groping for
the biggest rock he can find.

00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:35.040
Here a Brown Acre is
just a landscape.

00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:36.340
Brown Acre.

00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:41.950
"After the clear plastic sheeting
has been pulled back; folded away.

00:17:41.950 --> 00:17:45.650
After each woody rhizome has
been pried loose from the soil.

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:49.420
Each snarl of root traced
to its capillary ends.

00:17:49.420 --> 00:17:51.960
Twigs and petals tossed aside.

00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:54.600
Worms reburied elsewhere.

00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:57.860
After the soil has been
rubbed through a sieve.

00:17:57.860 --> 00:18:02.180
After the ground has been leveled
with rakes and stakes and string,

00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:05.680
no need for further
labor; further motion.

00:18:05.680 --> 00:18:07.710
Nothing has been sewn.

00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:10.710
Nothing is germinating
in the raw dirt.

00:18:10.710 --> 00:18:14.880
The light strikes each
granule the same as any other.

00:18:14.880 --> 00:18:19.450
A windlessness rises;
becomes a precondition.

00:18:19.450 --> 00:18:23.800
Why is it hard to admit
you couldn't live here?

00:18:23.800 --> 00:18:25.890
No one could live here.

00:18:25.890 --> 00:18:28.330 position:56%
This is not the texture of the real.

00:18:28.330 --> 00:18:31.870
Lacking attachment; lacking event.

00:18:31.870 --> 00:18:35.110
This is neither landscape
nor memory.

00:18:35.110 --> 00:18:36.530
This is parable.

00:18:36.530 --> 00:18:38.630
A caricature of restraint.

00:18:38.630 --> 00:18:41.790
But why does this shame you?

00:18:41.790 --> 00:18:45.440
Even now you're trying to hide
that your gaze is drifting upward.

00:18:45.440 --> 00:18:48.510
This plainness cannot
hold your attention.

00:18:48.510 --> 00:18:52.690
You're searching the sky for
some marker of time; of change.

00:18:52.690 --> 00:18:55.760
In a cloudless sky
the sun beats down.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:58.710
But if you observe that
the sun warms the soil.

00:18:58.710 --> 00:19:02.880
You must also concede that
the soil will grow colder.

00:19:02.880 --> 00:19:05.720
The sun stains only the body.

00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:09.160
And the body is what is
simply not an issue here."

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:14.920
And then this is another
poem called "Brown Acre",

00:19:16.070 --> 00:19:21.790
which I think is pretty
straight forward.

00:19:21.790 --> 00:19:23.720
"Brown Acre".

00:19:23.720 --> 00:19:26.550
"We were sitting, leaning
back against the house

00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:29.070
on the stone patio or terrace.

00:19:29.070 --> 00:19:32.230
Looking out over a steep
drop at the mountains arrayed

00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:34.300
in a semicircle around us.

00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:39.590 position:56%
All expectant angles, like the
music stands of an absent orchestra.

00:19:39.590 --> 00:19:43.620
Summer colors; orangey
golds and dims blues.

00:19:43.620 --> 00:19:45.790
And there must've been
greens as well.

00:19:45.790 --> 00:19:48.270
I wasn't paying attention.

00:19:48.270 --> 00:19:51.730
I was watching the thing
you had just said to me,

00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:54.590 position:56%
still hanging in the air between us.

00:19:54.590 --> 00:19:59.310
Its surfaces beading up with
a shiny liquid-like contempt.

00:19:59.310 --> 00:20:02.780
That might have been seeping
from the words themselves,

00:20:02.780 --> 00:20:06.800
or else condensing from the
air its inscrutable humidity.

00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:09.880
The droplets rounding
themselves as they fall.

00:20:09.880 --> 00:20:12.990
Edging a darker patch
on the patio tiles.

00:20:12.990 --> 00:20:16.710
A deepening concavity, and
above it a roughness in the air.

00:20:16.710 --> 00:20:20.700
The molecules of concrete
coalescing grain-by-grain

00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:23.840
into a corrugated pillar
topped by a cloud.

00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:28.150
A tree form, not a
sapling or a mountain tree.

00:20:28.150 --> 00:20:31.980
But a tree that would look at
home in a farmyard or a meadow.

00:20:31.980 --> 00:20:33.600
Sheltered from winds.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:37.710
Branches stretching out with all
confidence toward the horizon.

00:20:37.710 --> 00:20:42.640
A shape that should have been an
emblem of sufficiency; of calm.

00:20:42.640 --> 00:20:46.390
But whose surfaces were teaming
with a turbulent rush of particles,

00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:49.190
like the inner workings
of a throat exposed.

00:20:49.190 --> 00:20:52.390
And whose dimensions were
expanding with shocking speed.

00:20:52.390 --> 00:20:53.830
Accumulating mass.

00:20:53.830 --> 00:20:56.630
Accumulating coherence
and righteousness.

00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:59.100
Pulling more and more of
the disintegrating teras

00:20:59.100 --> 00:21:02.630
into its form taller than
us, then shadowing us,

00:21:02.630 --> 00:21:05.320
and doubtlessly underground
a root system

00:21:05.320 --> 00:21:07.940
of corresponding complexity
and spread.

00:21:07.940 --> 00:21:10.480
Was funneling down
displaced nothingness

00:21:10.480 --> 00:21:12.000
from a hole in the upper air.

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:17.580 position:56%
And then it was time, and I stood up
and went inside and shut the door.

00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:21.170
Unsure what still anchored
us to the mountainside."

00:21:21.170 --> 00:21:26.460
And I'll end with this.

00:21:26.460 --> 00:21:29.840
This is a strange poem.

00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:32.380
It's basically -- I think
like a lot of poems;

00:21:32.380 --> 00:21:34.450
like a lot of legal
opinions, it brings a lot

00:21:34.450 --> 00:21:36.010
of contradictory things together.

00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:41.640
So partially, a memory
from junior high school

00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:45.120
where a Twinkie [background
laughter],

00:21:45.120 --> 00:21:48.060
we had come to understand,
or we were told,

00:21:48.060 --> 00:21:50.070
was not a baked good
[background laughter].

00:21:50.070 --> 00:21:53.230
It was -- actually, you know,
what we were told was it was

00:21:53.230 --> 00:21:58.340
like this kind of tube of paste
that was extruded, and then exposed

00:21:58.340 --> 00:22:01.370
to some sort of catalyzing
chemical so it'd grow this kind

00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:04.850
of golden foamy outer layer, right?

00:22:04.850 --> 00:22:08.480
You know, and then they sort of
tinted the bottom of it brown

00:22:08.480 --> 00:22:11.800
with some tints of some kind
to make it appear baked.

00:22:11.800 --> 00:22:15.470
And this is what I believed for
decades [background laughter].

00:22:15.470 --> 00:22:18.150
Up until a couple of years
ago, actually [laughs].

00:22:18.150 --> 00:22:19.920
You know, I just thought, "Oh,
okay it's not a baked good.

00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.170
That's why its shelf
life is so long."

00:22:22.170 --> 00:22:25.540
And unfortunately, this
turned out not to be true.

00:22:25.540 --> 00:22:28.930
But, you know, Gold Acre
is also, you know, acre --

00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:32.670
when you're thinking of acre
legacy, you're also you know,

00:22:32.670 --> 00:22:34.420
obviously thinking about identity.

00:22:34.420 --> 00:22:36.260
You're also, you know, obviously
thinking about identity.

00:22:36.260 --> 00:22:37.560
You're thinking specifically
about race.

00:22:37.560 --> 00:22:42.360
And as I have a son and I'm
thinking of raising him,

00:22:42.360 --> 00:22:44.030
you know, as a Korean-American.

00:22:44.030 --> 00:22:47.090
And I think, well, you know, as
an immigrant who was born here,

00:22:47.090 --> 00:22:50.990
my own relationship to
being Korean-American is not

00:22:50.990 --> 00:22:52.730
exactly authentic.

00:22:52.730 --> 00:22:54.240
I don't speak the language.

00:22:54.240 --> 00:22:56.730
I'm not the person who can tell
you what the best thing to order

00:22:56.730 --> 00:22:59.800
on the menu is at every
Korean restaurant.

00:22:59.800 --> 00:23:01.810
You know, and what does it
mean to be, you know -- ?

00:23:01.810 --> 00:23:05.630 position:56%
So that made me think of the other
junior high school sense of Twinkie,

00:23:05.630 --> 00:23:09.480
which is someone yellow on the
outside and white on the inside.

00:23:09.480 --> 00:23:11.980
I think, you know,
lawyers might enjoy --

00:23:11.980 --> 00:23:15.750
lawyers are always grammar nerds,
so the other thing to notice

00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:18.700
about this poem is it's all cast
in the subjunctive, you know?

00:23:18.700 --> 00:23:20.000
The "as if it were".

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:25.730
The subjunctive is the mode
in which we express fantasy

00:23:25.730 --> 00:23:27.300
or the improbable.

00:23:27.300 --> 00:23:31.480
And one interesting thing about the
English language in particular is,

00:23:31.480 --> 00:23:33.940
our fantasy mode is
often indistinguishable

00:23:33.940 --> 00:23:35.550
from the past tense.

00:23:35.550 --> 00:23:39.660
So it's, you know, you -- so
sometimes we often tend to think

00:23:39.660 --> 00:23:44.020
of the past as if it were our --
you know, the past becomes a kind

00:23:44.020 --> 00:23:47.570
of fantasy, and often
a racial fantasy.

00:23:47.570 --> 00:23:50.230
"Gold Acre".

00:23:50.230 --> 00:23:55.590
"As if you were ever wide-eyed
enough to believe in urban legends.

00:23:55.590 --> 00:23:59.510
As if these plot elements
weren't the stalest of clichés.

00:23:59.510 --> 00:24:00.810
The secret lab.

00:24:00.810 --> 00:24:02.420
The anaerobic chamber.

00:24:02.420 --> 00:24:03.720
The gloved hand.

00:24:03.720 --> 00:24:05.020
Ex Machina.

00:24:05.020 --> 00:24:07.500
The chemical infused fog.

00:24:07.500 --> 00:24:10.280
As if every origin's
story didn't center

00:24:10.280 --> 00:24:14.480
on the same sweet myth
of a lost wholeness.

00:24:14.480 --> 00:24:19.940
As if such longing would seem more
palatable if packaged as nostalgia.

00:24:19.940 --> 00:24:24.570
As if inner and outer were merely
phases of the same substance.

00:24:24.570 --> 00:24:28.850
As if this whiteness had
been your original condition.

00:24:28.850 --> 00:24:31.810
As if it hadn't been
what is piped into you.

00:24:31.810 --> 00:24:34.130
What seeped into each vacant cell.

00:24:34.130 --> 00:24:35.430
Each airhole.

00:24:35.430 --> 00:24:36.730
Each pore.

00:24:36.730 --> 00:24:39.220
As if you had started out skinless.

00:24:39.220 --> 00:24:40.570
Shameless.

00:24:40.570 --> 00:24:41.870
Blameless.

00:24:41.870 --> 00:24:43.650
Creamy, as if whipped.

00:24:43.650 --> 00:24:45.790
Passive as if extruded.

00:24:45.790 --> 00:24:49.290
Quivering with volatility
in a metal mold.

00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:53.850
As if a catalyzing vapor
triggered a latent reaction.

00:24:53.850 --> 00:24:55.600
As if your flesh foamed

00:24:55.600 --> 00:25:01.210
up a hydrogenated emulsion
consisting mostly of trapped air.

00:25:01.210 --> 00:25:06.710
As if though sponge-like, you could
remain shelf-stable for decades.

00:25:06.710 --> 00:25:08.250
Part embalming fluid.

00:25:08.250 --> 00:25:09.810
Part rocket fuel.

00:25:09.810 --> 00:25:11.450
Part glue.

00:25:11.450 --> 00:25:15.750
As if you had been named
twin, a word for likeness.

00:25:15.750 --> 00:25:18.540
Or wink a word for joke.

00:25:18.540 --> 00:25:21.280
Or ink, a word for stain.

00:25:21.280 --> 00:25:24.820
Or key, a word for answer.

00:25:24.820 --> 00:25:28.790
As if your skin oxidized to
its present burnished hue.

00:25:28.790 --> 00:25:31.400
Golden, as if homemade.

00:25:31.400 --> 00:25:33.200
Thank you.

